                                                                                               Another example of granularization to support control assessments is the case of a privacy
                                                                                               control requirement not being applicable to a particular system (e.g., the system does not
                                                                                               process personally identifiable information); assessors can disregard such non-applicable
                                                                                               requirements and still find that the control is satisfied. Figure 2 provides an example of control
                                                                                               CM-04 25, which is further granularized to address security impacts in CM-04[01] and privacy
                                                                                               impacts in CM-04[02].

